Mayday! Mayday!

125
00:11:49,066 --> 00:11:50,000
Who the hell are they?

126
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,534
Why are they attacking us?!

127
00:11:51,533 --> 00:11:52,100
Here they come!

128
00:11:52,100 --> 00:11:53,501
H-Help us!

129
00:11:55,566 --> 00:11:57,234
When did this happen?

130
00:11:57,966 --> 00:12:01,102
lt has been sent through the
booster relays a few times.

131
00:12:01,100 --> 00:12:02,801
The footage is three days old.

132
00:12:03,833 --> 00:12:06,135
Why were they attacked?

133
00:12:07,066 --> 00:12:09,168
This is a massacre!

134
00:12:09,399 --> 00:12:10,801
Who's the enemy?

135
00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:13,168
We don't know.

136
00:12:13,166 --> 00:12:14,467
Chief.

137
00:12:14,466 --> 00:12:16,301
Shouldn't we postpone the departure

138
00:12:16,299 --> 00:12:20,570
of the Third Emigration Fleet until
we know more about the situation?

139
00:12:20,566 --> 00:12:25,070
We can't send transpoR ships there
knowing they will be destroyed!

140
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:27,735
Continue as planned.

141
00:12:28,633 --> 00:12:29,667
With all due respect...

142
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:33,268
Has Kodai returned yet?

143
00:12:34,366 --> 00:12:34,933
Kodai-san?

144
00:12:36,866 --> 00:12:41,804
He's the only one who can save
the Earth from this danger.

145
00:12:41,766 --> 00:12:44,702
We don't have much time.

146
00:12:45,833 --> 00:12:48,969
Chief, we've been contacted by the Solar System
Communication Bureau.

147
00:12:48,966 --> 00:12:50,200
Displaying transmission on screen B.

148
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:50,900
Okay.

149
00:12:51,466 --> 00:12:54,101
This is the Solar System
Communication Bureau.

150
00:12:54,100 --> 00:12:57,603
Deep space cargo vesseI Yuki wIl be be warping
out within the system.

151
00:12:59,333 --> 00:13:00,667
Kodai...

152
00:13:00,666 --> 00:13:01,867
You've come back...

153
00:13:15,399 --> 00:13:16,834
Excuse me, Captain.

154
00:13:16,866 --> 00:13:18,901
We're ready to warp out.

155
00:13:18,899 --> 00:13:20,368
Okay, l'll be right there.

156
00:13:21,166 --> 00:13:22,901
lt's been three years, huh.

157
00:13:25,133 --> 00:13:27,802
l bet your daughter has
grown up into a fine lady.

158
00:13:33,399 --> 00:13:33,967
Yeah.

159
00:13:39,433 --> 00:13:41,268
We're finishing our lastjump.

160
00:13:41,266 --> 00:13:42,500
We've finally returned to Earth!

161
00:14:06,533 --> 00:14:07,901
Aquarius.

162
00:14:46,033 --> 00:14:50,871
This observation footage has been colored, processed
and fast-forwarded

163
00:14:50,833 --> 00:14:52,568
to make it easy to understand.

164
00:14:53,233 --> 00:14:54,601
l hadn't expected this...

165
00:14:55,266 --> 00:14:59,570
This is a black hole that doesn't move according to
any pattern we've observed.

166
00:14:59,566 --> 00:15:04,504
We're calling it the
''Cascading Black Hole. ''

167
00:15:05,100 --> 00:15:06,301
Yes, sir.

168
00:15:11,833 --> 00:15:15,570
Are we certain it will devourthe Earth?

169
00:15:15,533 --> 00:15:17,334
Yes.

170
00:15:17,299 --> 00:15:19,535
We have run the
calculations over and over.

171
00:15:19,533 --> 00:15:23,236
We are certain that it's passing
through the Solar System.

172
00:15:23,233 --> 00:15:24,701
lt's unavoidable.

173
00:15:24,700 --> 00:15:29,971
We estimate eight million seconds
before it reaches Earth.

174
00:15:30,566 --> 00:15:35,270
ln other words, Earth has just three
months left until its destruction.

175
00:15:35,233 --> 00:15:36,534
Yes.

176
00:15:36,833 --> 00:15:41,103
We first observed this black
hole three years ago.

177
00:15:42,299 --> 00:15:45,836
We gathered astronomers
from all around the world,

178
00:15:45,799 --> 00:15:48,435
and organized daily conferences
to discuss countermeasures.

179
00:15:48,433 --> 00:15:52,270
Altering the black hole's
trajectoy, destroying it...

180
00:15:52,266 --> 00:15:54,635
terraforming one of the frontier planets

181
00:15:54,666 --> 00:15:56,834
and temporarily taking shelterthere...

182
00:15:56,799 --> 00:16:00,270
They even looked into
shifting the Earth's orbit.

183
00:16:00,933 --> 00:16:02,801
Eventually, they came to the conclusion

184
00:16:02,833 --> 00:16:07,537
that none of these possibilities were
feasible with our current technology.

185
00:16:07,933 --> 00:16:12,270
Mankind's only hope is to seek
refuge in the vastness ofspace.

186
00:16:12,233 --> 00:16:16,236
l've put Shima-kun in charge
ofthe emigration plans,

187
00:16:16,200 --> 00:16:20,637
and finalized the preparations forthe evacuation of mankind
while helping them understand this decision.

188
00:16:20,633 --> 00:16:25,437
l've heard that the crew ofthe salvaged ship was
escorting people to Amarl.

189
00:16:25,799 --> 00:16:26,734
lndeed.

190
00:16:26,766 --> 00:16:29,235
Amarl is located in the Sairam System.

191
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:32,136
Our destination is its moon.

192
00:16:33,866 --> 00:16:36,235
Will we be able to
create a second Earth?

193
00:16:37,366 --> 00:16:41,303
This is the route ofthe
Second Emigration Fleet.

194
00:16:41,266 --> 00:16:42,834
Displaying map on screen C.

195
00:16:44,833 --> 00:16:47,468
Any intel on the fleet that attacked us?

196
00:16:47,899 --> 00:16:50,535
No, we have no intel on them yet.

197
00:16:58,466 --> 00:17:02,436
Will the Earth vanish...

198
00:17:02,399 --> 00:17:03,701
without leaving behind a trace?

199
00:17:05,099 --> 00:17:08,269
This planet that the
Yamato has protected...

200
00:17:08,266 --> 00:17:09,333
lndeed.

201
