611
00:52:39,433 --> 00:52:41,535
Distance: 18 space km.

612
00:52:41,500 --> 00:52:43,235
Kamijou, deploy the heavy bomber.

613
00:52:43,233 --> 00:52:44,067
Yes, sir!

614
00:52:56,699 --> 00:53:00,703
Heavy bomber, attack the hostile at 4:30 port of
the emigrant vessels.

615
00:53:00,699 --> 00:53:01,400
Roger!

616
00:54:01,266 --> 00:54:01,966
Now!

617
00:54:01,966 --> 00:54:02,866
Fire!

618
00:54:02,833 --> 00:54:03,833
Yes, sir.

619
00:54:03,833 --> 00:54:06,435
Prepare first and second batteries.

620
00:54:08,166 --> 00:54:09,133
Fire!

621
00:54:11,099 --> 00:54:12,935
Launch bow torpedoes!

622
00:54:24,366 --> 00:54:26,334
What are they doing?

623
00:54:28,599 --> 00:54:30,335
lt's that ship...

624
00:54:30,300 --> 00:54:36,639
That ship is encouraging the whole
fleet and increasing their power.

625
00:54:36,633 --> 00:54:38,768
That ship?

626
00:54:38,766 --> 00:54:40,334
Aim for that ship.

627
00:54:40,333 --> 00:54:42,134
Forget about the others.

628
00:54:42,099 --> 00:54:44,635
Blow that ship to smithereens!

629
00:54:45,300 --> 00:54:45,967
Yes, sir!

630
00:54:55,666 --> 00:54:56,900
Damn that Gorui...

631
00:54:56,866 --> 00:54:59,835
Having trouble against a fleet like that.

632
00:54:59,833 --> 00:55:02,001
He's not worth my attention.

633
00:55:04,566 --> 00:55:08,236
Escort ships Hatsuyuki
and Shirayuki are down.

634
00:55:08,199 --> 00:55:09,834
Explosions in the Asagiri.

635
00:55:09,800 --> 00:55:13,403
The enemy is moving
toward the black hole.

636
00:55:14,099 --> 00:55:17,169
How far along are the emigrant vessels?

637
00:55:17,166 --> 00:55:19,801
880/o ofthem have warped.

638
00:55:21,133 --> 00:55:24,870
Attention all escoR ships,
pull back as you fight,

639
00:55:24,866 --> 00:55:27,602
and prepare to warp after
the emigration fleet.

640
00:55:27,566 --> 00:55:29,467
The Yamato will take
care ofthe enemy fleet!

641
00:55:35,233 --> 00:55:38,603
All fighters, help the
escort force to withdraw!

642
00:55:52,233 --> 00:55:53,233
Damn!

643
00:55:53,533 --> 00:55:55,568
l'll kill them for sure!

644
00:55:56,233 --> 00:55:58,902
Prepare the wave-motion cannon!

645
00:56:01,300 --> 00:56:03,201
Don't get carried away, Kamijou!

646
00:56:03,233 --> 00:56:06,336
lt's pointless to use the wave-motion
cannon against a scattered fleet!

647
00:56:07,199 --> 00:56:08,868
Not only is it ine_ective,

648
00:56:09,333 --> 00:56:12,569
but it will cost the Yamato
the energy it needs to warp.

649
00:56:14,199 --> 00:56:15,834
l'm sorry.

650
00:56:44,300 --> 00:56:47,469
This fleet is completely di_erent from the one we
defeated the other day.

651
00:56:47,433 --> 00:56:48,600
lt's because ofthat ship.

652
00:56:49,800 --> 00:56:55,172
Such a sublime decision... not to
Iose even a single emigrant vessel.

653
00:56:55,133 --> 00:56:58,636
Their spirit is what makes their command ofthe
whole fleet so extraordinay.

654
00:56:58,633 --> 00:57:02,136
You seem to admire the enemy.

655
00:57:03,500 --> 00:57:07,804
ls this really the way an invader fights?

656
00:57:08,800 --> 00:57:13,905
l feel a strong will to live,
rather than to invade.

657
00:57:13,866 --> 00:57:17,102
What we are doing is no
di_erent than a massacre.

658
00:57:17,833 --> 00:57:21,436
That ship on the other hand...

659
00:57:29,300 --> 00:57:30,334
Rapid turn!

660
00:57:36,666 --> 00:57:38,701
Captain! What are you doing?

661
00:57:39,099 --> 00:57:42,136
Kamijou, shoot randomly at that ship!

662
00:57:42,099 --> 00:57:42,900
Yes, sir!

663
00:58:03,866 --> 00:58:05,634
Cease the attack!

664
00:58:07,033 --> 00:58:07,833
Why?

665
00:58:08,533 --> 00:58:13,104
Don't you think that it would be
regrettable to bury that enemy?

666
00:58:13,066 --> 00:58:14,734
lndeed.

667
00:58:15,133 --> 00:58:19,604
lt's frantically trying to protect the emigrant vessels by
risking its own life.

668
00:58:20,466 --> 00:58:25,137
We used to have that soldierly spirit.

669
00:58:25,133 --> 00:58:26,734
But look at us now...

670
00:58:26,699 --> 00:58:32,072
Now we are bound to that parvenu SUS
and helping to massacre people.

671
00:58:32,066 --> 00:58:35,402
Don't you think we should stop
degrading ourselves any further?

672
00:58:36,599 --> 00:58:38,735
lt's something only you'd say, Admiral.

673
00:58:40,133 --> 00:58:42,602
Cease the attack, Captain.

674
00:58:42,599 --> 00:58:43,567
Understood, sir.

675
00:58:44,533 --> 00:58:47,669
Attention Ethos fleet, cease fire!

676
00:58:51,099 --> 00:58:52,568
Full speed ahead!

677
00:58:54,699 --> 00:58:55,901
Where are we going?

678
00:58:56,666 --> 00:58:59,769
We must regain our honor.

679
00:59:14,400 --> 00:59:16,201
Enemy fire has stopped.

680
00:59:16,599 --> 00:59:17,400
What?

681
00:59:17,699 --> 00:59:19,068
All fighters, hury up!

682
00:59:29,699 --> 00:59:32,069
Captain, there's an incoming
transmission from that ship.

683
00:59:32,466 --> 00:59:33,200
What?

684
00:59:33,166 --> 00:59:34,367
Put it on the panel.

685
00:59:37,300 --> 00:59:42,738
l'm the Commander in Chief o1 Planet
Ethos's fleet, Admiral Gorui.

686
00:59:42,733 --> 00:59:46,169
l highly admire your
eflort on the battlefield.

687
00:59:46,800 --> 00:59:51,004
Would you tell me the name
of the captain and his ship?

688
00:59:51,699 --> 00:59:55,003
EaRh Defense Force Space
Battleship Yamato.

689
00:59:54,966 --> 00:59:57,568
l'm the Captain, Kodai Susumu.

690
00:59:58,000 --> 01:00:01,703
Space Battleship
Yamato... Captain Kodai.

691
01:00:01,699 --> 01:00:04,135
l'll be frank now.

692
01:00:04,099 --> 01:00:06,769
The Ethos military has
many excellent allies,

693
01:00:06,766 --> 01:00:10,102
and it also respects formidable enemies.

694
01:00:10,099 --> 01:00:11,367
This is an old tradition.

695
01:00:11,766 --> 01:00:13,634
lf l cannot protect this honor,

696
01:00:13,599 --> 01:00:16,703
l'd chose an honorable
death like the Yamato.

697
01:00:17,433 --> 01:00:19,034
l'd like to ask you, Admiral Gorei.

698
01:00:19,800 --> 01:00:21,868
Why are you attacking us?

699
01:00:22,500 --> 01:00:26,303
lt's decision of the Greater
Urup InterstellarAlliance.

700
01:00:26,266 --> 01:00:30,169
The leadership ofthe union
has been grabbed by the SUS.

701
01:00:30,766 --> 01:00:32,534
The SUS...

702
01:00:32,900 --> 01:00:38,705
But this massacre is nothing but an irrational
way of demonstrating their power.

703
01:00:38,666 --> 01:00:45,139
Therefore, l deeply respect your e_orts ofsaving
the emigration fleet from them.

704
01:00:47,866 --> 01:00:51,069
l appreciate that, Admiral Gorui.

705
01:00:52,099 --> 01:00:54,068
Good luck.

706
01:01:22,433 --> 01:01:26,603
What's the meaning ofthis, Gorui?

707
01:01:26,599 --> 01:01:30,437
l'm only following the
Ethos military honor code.

708
01:01:30,933 --> 01:01:37,806
Does the honor code ofthe Ethos military state to defy the
decision ofthe Greater Urup InterstellarAlliance?

709
01:01:37,766 --> 01:01:43,004
lsn't that the will of the SUS,
rather than that ofthe Alliance?

710
01:01:43,466 --> 01:01:49,004
l assume you know the
consequences ofdefying us.

711
01:01:49,000 --> 01:01:51,635
Oh, what are you going to do?

712
01:01:53,500 --> 01:01:57,303
lfyou ever defy my orders again,

713
01:01:57,300 --> 01:02:01,437
l'll not only destroy you,
but your whole planet!

714
01:02:02,033 --> 01:02:03,734
Keep that in mind.

715
01:02:05,300 --> 01:02:07,368
Destroy Ethos?

716
01:02:10,366 --> 01:02:15,437
No matter what happens, our
citizens will understand.

717
01:02:22,000 --> 01:02:23,968
Attention all emigrant vessels.

718
01:02:23,966 --> 01:02:25,801
We're about to arrive at Amarl.

719
01:02:25,766 --> 01:02:27,000
Finalize your preparations.

720
01:02:28,266 --> 01:02:30,635
Kobayashi, you can switch back now.

721
01:02:30,633 --> 01:02:31,433
Yes, sir.

722
01:03:15,966 --> 01:03:17,267
lt's the Yamato!

723
01:03:17,699 --> 01:03:19,034
The Yamato has come!

724
01:03:19,033 --> 01:03:19,900
lndeed.

725
01:03:19,900 --> 01:03:21,101
Wow!

726
01:03:48,733 --> 01:03:52,203
Thank heavens this emigration
fleet made it safely here.

727
01:04:00,666 --> 01:04:02,868
Looks like the emigrants
are doing fine here.

728
01:04:02,866 --> 01:04:03,199
Yes.

729
01:04:04,199 --> 01:04:06,068
